# Table

Tables provide structure to data sets enabling a customer to scan, analyze, compare, filter, sort and/or manipulate data.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/table
```

```tsx
import { Table } from '@ids-ts/table';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `density` | `Density` | No | - |
| `border` | `Border` | No | * The type of border to surround the table |
| `stickyColumns` | `boolean` | No | * Flag to indicate if table needs column to be sticky |
| `divider` | `Divider` | No | - |
| `verticalDividerStyle` | `VerticalDividerStyle` | No | - |
| `striped` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `hover` | `Hover` | No | * Show some love to either the rows or columns on hover |
| `Pin` | `pins the first column, with content flowing und...` | Yes | - |
| `addons` | `React.ReactElement` | No | A slot for additional table things |
| `wrapperProps` | `Omit<Element<'div'>, 'children'>` | No | Props to pass to the root div element. Rest props are spread on the table |
| `disableScrollWrapper` | `boolean` | No | To disable scrollwrapper if needed |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface TableProps {
  /**
   * How spacious to make each of the cells
   *
   * @default 'comfortable'
   */
  density?: Density;
  /**
   * The type of border to surround the table
   */
  border?: Border;
  /**
   * Flag to indicate if table needs column to be sticky
   */
  stickyColumns?: boolean;
  /**
   * Where to put the dividers between cells
   *
   * @default false
   */
  divider?: Divider;
  /**
   * The line style for the vertical divider. Only affects vertical dividers.
   *
   * @default 'dotted'
   */
  verticalDividerStyle?: VerticalDividerStyle;
  /**
   * Zebras are cool. Stripe the rows.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  striped?: boolean;

  /**
   * Show some love to either the rows or columns on hover
   */
  hover?: Hover;

  /**
   * How the table should behave on mobile
   * Pin: pins the first column, with content flowing underneath it
   * Elevated: pins the first column, but elevates it above the other rows.
   * Stack: stacks the rows on top of each other, merging the data into sections
   *
   * @default pin
   */
  responsive?: Responsive;

  /** A slot for additional table things */
  addons?: React.ReactElement;
  /** Props to pass to the root div element. Rest props are spread on the table */
  wrapperProps?: Omit<Element<'div'>, 'children'>;
  /** To disable scrollwrapper if needed */
  disableScrollWrapper?: boolean;
}

export type Density = 'roomy' | 'comfortable' | 'cozy' | 'compact';

export type Border = 'square' | 'round' | undefined;

export type Divider = 'horizontal' | 'vertical' | boolean;

export type VerticalDividerStyle = 'dotted' | 'solid';

export type Hover = 'row' | 'cell' | undefined;

export type Responsive = 'pin' | 'elevate' | 'stack' | 'merge-and-stack';
```

</details>

## Token Usage

### Color

**action** — Interactive element colors and hover/active/focus states
- `--color-action-complementary`
- `--color-action-complementary-active`
- `--color-action-complementary-border`

**text** — Primary and secondary text colors
- `--color-text-accent`
- `--color-text-complementary`
- `--color-text-disabled`

**divider** — Divider and separator line colors
- `--color-divider-inverse`
- `--color-divider-primary`
- `--color-divider-secondary`

### Space

**component** — Component-level spacing (padding, gap)
- `--space-component-gap-large`
- `--space-component-gap-medium`
- `--space-component-gap-small`

### Font

**font** — Font family, size, weight, and line height
- `--font-size-12`
- `--font-size-14`
- `--font-size-16`

## Usage Patterns

### Basic

```tsx
() => (
  <Table
    density="comfortable"
    divider="horizontal"
    responsive="elevate"
    summary="contributors to the consumer group design systems table component"
  >
    <Table.Header divider="horizontal">
      <Table.Row>
        <Table.Cell>First name</Table.Cell>
        <Table.Cell>Last name</Table.Cell>
        <Table.Cell>City</Table.Cell>
        <Table.Cell>State</Table.Cell>
        <Table.Cell>Team</Table.Cell>
      </Table.Row>
    </Table.Header>
    <Table.Body>
      {data.map((item, index) => {
        const id = `row-${index}`;
        return (
          <Table.Row key={id}>
            <Table.Cell>{item.firstName}</Table.Cell>
            <Table.Cell>{item.lastName}</Table.Cell>
            <Table.Cell>{item.city}</Table.Cell>
            <Table.Cell>{item.state}</Table.Cell>
            <Table.Cell>{item.team}</Table.Cell>
          </Table.Row>
        );
      })
```

### With Action Column

```tsx
() => {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  const handleOpen = () => setOpen(true);
  const handleClose = () => setOpen(false);

  return (
    <Table
      density="comfortable"
      divider="horizontal"
      responsive="elevate"
      summary="contributors to the consumer group design systems table component"
    >
      <Table.Header divider="horizontal">
        <Table.Row>
          <Table.Cell>First name</Table.Cell>
          <Table.Cell>Last name</Table.Cell>
          <Table.Cell>City</Table.Cell>
          <Table.Cell>State</Table.Cell>
          <Table.Cell>Team</Table.Cell>
          <Table.Cell style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Action</Table.Cell>
        </Table.Row>
      </Table.Header>
      <Table.Body>
        {data.map((item, index) => {
          const id = `row-${index}`;
          return (
            <Table.Row key={id}>
              <Table.Cell>{item.firstName}</Table.Cell>
              <Table.Cell>{item.lastName}</Table.Cell>
              <Table.Cell>{item.city}</Table.Cell>
              <Table.Cell>{item.state}</Table.Cell>
              <Table.Cell>{item.team}</Table.Cell>
              <Table.Cell style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>
                <Button size="small" onClick={handleOpen}>
                  View
                </Button>
              </Table.Cell>
            </Table.Row>
          );
        })}
      </Table.Body>
      <ToastMessage
        open={open}
        onClose={handleClose}
        onActionClick={handleClose}
      >
        View button clicked
      </ToastMessage>
    </Table>
  );
}
```

